##Dr. Cha of the shanghai-hubei medical team has two "post-epidemic wishes"

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Keeping a journal is not only a way to keep track of her work, it's also a great way for her to decompress.

By Huang Qiyuan Huiyun

On the evening of the first day of the New Year, Dr. Cha Qiongfang of Renji hospital, affiliated to Shanghai Jiaotong University Medical College, wrote the first "war diary" in his hotel room in Wuhan.
From the early New Year's Day (January 23) , to the New Year's Eve departure, and then to the arrival in Wuhan for pre-service training, Foshan doctor experienced a special two days and nights, emotional ups and downs. At the Training Meeting, the team leader specifically charged that we should restore a calm state of mind, calm to deal with the next hard fight.
Returning to his room after the training, Dr. Cha decided to cool off from the recording work. She said that the first diary is actually a work report, mainly to report to the unit leaders in Shanghai after arriving in Wuhan, to colleagues to report a safe, but also to sort out the mood.

But unexpectedly, from that day on, the diary did not fall a day, so far has written 22.
Later, she found that keeping a diary was not only a way to keep track of her work, but also a good way to relieve her stress.
Dr. Cha worked at Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, the first in Wuhan to focus on new cases of coronary pneumonia, and the sickest in the intensive care unit taken over by the Shanghai medical team. The intensity and stress of the work of the medical staff can be imagined.

Although usually the work at Yan Chai Hospital is also very hard, but this is the first time in a highly contagious epidemic, and working in a high risk intensive-care unit, is a completely different kind of pressure for Cha.
Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, initially because there is no heating equipment, the first night shift after the red hands of the nurses caused social concern. Dr. Cha said that today, the community donated a lot of materials, Ward with a "small Sun" , pasted warm baby, and some people donated coats, working at night is not cold, "compared to the first time is simply heaven and earth. ".
If it is not the epidemic, Dr. Cha ready to mother to his home, usually busy with work, not much to see, the New Year holiday mother to the side, is her greatest desire. Her two fridges are packed with years of food, as if she were the annual New Year's Eve dinner, a feast for a dozen or so people as she cooks for her extended family.
Dr Cha said there was also a wish to awaken naturally during the Spring Festival. As the head of a ward in the Department of Respiratory Medicine at Yan Chai Hospital and a senior doctor, sleeping naturally is a rare luxury in a year, "something I've always dreamed of doing. ".
Little New Year's Eve received a call from the leadership, Dr. Cha qiong-fang did not hesitate to sign up for the medical team, "such a moment, do not come forward to excuse the title of Doctor, also excuse the title of Party member. ".
When it came to what to do after the outbreak ended, Dr. Zha's first wish was to unmask herself -- because she wore it for so long; her second wish was to go to a busy mall, "I used to dislike the crowds on the roads, but now I find that there is no one on the roads. I can only stay at home. It is also a very painful thing. Only when I lose it can I feel cherish it. ".

On this Special Valentine's Day, believe in the power of love
By Josephine Cha
February 14, Day twenty-one of Hubei Aid, rain in Wuhan.
Get up at 6:30, should be the dawn of the day, is still dark, sometimes lightning across the horizon, pouring rain from the sky. It has been three weeks since we arrived in Wuhan. It seems that this heavy rain is the first time we have seen it.
After breakfast, just out of the hotel door, the heavy rain gradually stopped. The thundershowers of spring come and go quickly. Instead of being crushed by the rainstorm, the flowers on the roadside trees gradually blossom after the rain. They stick their heads out from among the tender green branches and leaves, making people feel the power of life. The road by the side of the road is wet and needs a detour. After the rain, the weather, feeling particularly humid, wearing a mask to go to the gold and Silver Pool Hospital, although only a few minutes is a sweat.
It's rounds today. No isolation, just paperwork in the doctor's office.

The office atmosphere is a bit depressing, the original intubation of the patient or died, Professor Chen's virus inflammation storm theory was again verified. The three doctors on duty in the ICU had a busy night last night and were unable to get back to work. Everything I could think of, everything I needed to do: tracheal intubation, invasive ventilation, prone position ventilation, lung recruitment... And yet, the virus is still so aggressive in taking patients away.
At the end of the shift, we analyzed and summarized the death cases observed so far: the Airway without secretion, the Alveoli without expansion, the dysfunction of blood coagulation, the elevation of myocardial enzyme spectrum, the control of uncontrolled blood pressure, the control of fluid replacement... . .
Because from the major hospitals in Shanghai, we all have their own team behind the plan, team Zheng asked you for treatment whether there is a new idea. After everyone expressed their opinions, Zheng Team concluded the Treatment Direction: The first way is to be stable and strictly follow the guidelines, but it seems difficult to reduce the death rate of critically ill patients; the second way is to make steady progress, we can add potentially useful drugs to the guidelines; the third route is risky, if some of the drugs save lives, but only if they have to pass a medical ethics review.
Good news today, too. The first patient in our ICU was discharged today. All of our patients have been transferred to the light ward since they got better. They were not discharged from our ward at the time of statistics. For the first time in more than 20 days, we feel the joy of patients discharged from hospital: When the patient raised his thumb, we feel ecstatic that all the pay is worth it.

We have a couple in ICU, beds 15 and 6, who are both in isolation with a new case of coronary pneumonia. The wife in bed 15 is heavier and requires noninvasive ventilation; the husband in bed 6 is lighter and receives oxygen. The timid 15 bed all needs the person to accompany, the night is the nurse to accompany, even goes to the toilet also is to call the nurse to stand outside, the day is 6 bed patient many times past to accompany. Today is Valentine's Day, two people sit together, although no flowers, but a hand holding an apple, very "piously" asked our nurses to take a group photo. I think when they get out of the hospital, they'll always remember this special Valentine's Day.
Back at the hotel, our assistant team leader Zhang Mingming in the group post: "We are a group of good and responsible people, our silent pay is not noisy, but it is so warm. ". Although the epidemic has temporarily blocked our footsteps, but the heart and heart distance will not change. On this Special Valentine's Day, believe in the power of love."The team prepared Valentine's Day gifts for each member, a CHOCOLATE FERRERO SPA and a moisturizer, thanks to everyone for their quiet devotion.
We were Fed mcdonald's Burgers and Pineapple Pies for dinner. We felt full and loved, and even the three cream cakes we had prepared at the hotel were only to be seen.
